            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;I know that it&apos;s an old thread - I stumbled upon it. @Artem Nakonechny is technically right but the &lt;a href=&quot;https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7231#section-4.3.1&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noreferrer&quot;&gt;new spec&lt;/a&gt; says &lt;i&gt;&quot;A payload within a GET request message has no defined semantics; sending a payload body on a GET request might cause some existing implementations to reject the request.&quot;&lt;/i&gt;  So it&apos;s still not a really good idea if can be avoided.&lt;/span&gt;

              &lt;div class=&quot;d-inline-flex ai-center&quot;&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;/users/1061997/fastcatch&quot; title=&quot;755 reputation&quot; class=&quot;comment-user&quot;&gt;fastcatch&lt;/a&gt;
                &lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-date&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;comment-link&quot; href=&quot;#comment79934566_983458&quot;&gt;&lt;span title=&quot;2017-09-29 13:39:49Z, License: CC BY-SA 3.0&quot; class=&quot;relativetime-clean&quot;&gt;Sep 29, 2017 at 13:39&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;/div&gt;

            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;The Robustness Principle is flawed. If you are liberal in what you accept, you will get crap, if you have any success in terms of adoption, just because you accept crap. That will make it harder for you to evolve your interface. Just look at HTML. That&apos;s the reboustness principle in action.&lt;/span&gt;

              &lt;div class=&quot;d-inline-flex ai-center&quot;&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;/users/709537/evgeniy-berezovsky&quot; title=&quot;17,483 reputation&quot; class=&quot;comment-user&quot;&gt;Evgeniy Berezovsky&lt;/a&gt;
