                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-date&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;comment-link&quot; href=&quot;#comment37606568_22236708&quot;&gt;&lt;span title=&quot;2014-06-20 13:40:07Z, License: CC BY-SA 3.0&quot; class=&quot;relativetime-clean&quot;&gt;Jun 20, 2014 at 13:40&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;/div&gt;

            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;@CarLuva The POST section says &quot;The POST method is used to request that the origin server accept the entity enclosed...&quot; The &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.w3.org/Protocols/rfc2616/rfc2616-sec7.html#sec7.2&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noreferrer&quot;&gt;entity body&lt;/a&gt; section says &quot;The entity-body is obtained from the message-body...&quot; Therefore, the POST section does mention message body, although indirectly by referencing the entity body which is carried by the message body of the POST request.&lt;/span&gt;

              &lt;div class=&quot;d-inline-flex ai-center&quot;&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;/users/2136552/frederickf&quot; title=&quot;1,401 reputation&quot; class=&quot;comment-user&quot;&gt;frederickf&lt;/a&gt;
