                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;This is a bad requests because your payload isn&apos;t expected (or sensible) for a &lt;code&gt;GET&lt;/code&gt; &lt;i&gt;on that particular endpoint&lt;/i&gt; -- it has nothing to do with the use of &lt;code&gt;GET&lt;/code&gt; in the general case.  A random payload could break a &lt;code&gt;POST&lt;/code&gt; just as easily, and return the same &lt;code&gt;400 Bad Request&lt;/code&gt;, if the contents were not in a format that made sense in the context of the specific request.&lt;/span&gt;

